Original JP Fire Control Kit

This kit for .154 small pin receivers consists of a JP trigger with engagement and overtravel screws and disconnector spring installed as an assembly, disconnector, instructional video, and our standard array of springs: yellow reduced power trigger spring both yellow and red reduced power hammer springs.

Spring Selection Guide:

Competition/Recreation
The yellow/yellow combination may be used for competition and various recreational applications with hand loads or domestic-manufactured, non-military ammunition. It will result in a release weight in the 3.0-3.5 lb. range on most receivers.
Enhanced Ignition Reliability 
The yellow trigger spring combined with the red hammer spring will yield a release weight of 3.5-4.0 lbs. on most receivers and offers increased reliability for (5.56 NATO) or foreign-manufactured ammo with low sensitivity primers. The yellow-red springs must be used for any large-frame AR installation to ensure 100% ignition reliability. This is also the minimum acceptable combination for tactical duty (LE) installations and should be used only with domestic-manufactured ammo in this application.
Duty/Defense
The tactical spring set includes a full powers (grey) hammer spring (purchased separately) and yellow trigger spring. It may be required for agencies that mandate a trigger release weight of over 4 lbs. This set up also insures 100% ignition reliability on both AR-15 and AR-10 type rifles.
CMP
To meet NRA Service Rifle Competition rules of a 4.5 lb. release weight, the CMP spring set (purchased separately) includes the full-power hammer spring and a custom trigger return spring, which will allow you to tune to a release weight just over 4.5 pounds to lift the NRA weights.

title: For Sale/Trade:  CVC Helmet DH-132A (Large)
postcontent:
Hello, I am selling a DH132A CVC Helmet Large made by BAE Systems and has the helmet liner etc, Bose head phones, unsure if they work. No cracks in the kelvar, just some of the paint is chipping off, no big deal. The DH-132A is the second generation of the CVC DH 132 helmet designs. From what I've found on the internet

DH132- Is just a bump helmet
DH132A- Is a Kevlar helmet and has ballistic protection and is lighter than "B" Model
DH132B- Is thicker and heavier than the "A" but provides slightly more ballistic protection

I bought this wanting to make a SOHAH / FAST Helmet but I had the time or the money to do so. If you google CVC conversion or DH132 Conversion, or variest keywords you can see how it is done. I recommend using a OCC-Liner Kit either by the HK Air Soft Company FMA or getting the real deal Ops-Core one, but you can use a ACH/MICH . If you're a serious buyer I can send you links of what you'd need to do it, along with accessories like a ARC rail and VAS NVG Shroud. If you purchase I can give you a few tips I learned from the extensive time researching on the internet.

I'm looking to get $150 (this is FTF pick up off i205 and mill plain) out of it, that is how much I paid excluding shipping. Open to trades, tactical gear etc, let me know what you have.

Thank you for looking, Any question or additional pictures, feel free to ask.

title: For Sale:  Sako A7 Long Range Hunter 300 win mag
location: salt lake Stansbury, Salt Lake City, Utah
postcontent:
This is a Sako A7 long range hunter rifle in 300 win mag. This gun is basically brand new with extras. I added a Holland Muzzle brake $200 (brake can be removed if desired)and a 20MOA solid one piece base $80 and it comes with Warne 30mm Tactical scope rings $80. This is by far the sweetest firearm I have ever owned and I already regret selling it. I have shot less than four boxes of ammo through it for the break in period. It is a tack driver. The recoil is so light my 9 year old son shoots it with ease. I have friends with other heavier long range rifles that were puzzled when they tried this A7. Although the A7 is substantially lighter than their rifles, the A7 has much less felt recoil.
I cant think of a better long range gun it has an aluminum bedded fiberglass stock. A flited heavy 26″ barrel a 3 locking lug bolt with 70 degree operation and it comes with two factory magazines.

This is easy a sub MOA gun having achieved .75″ minus groups during break in, if someone taylored a load for it I am certain it would be a .5 minute gun. It is capeable of 1200 yard shots with the right scope.

I am selling this rifle because I just don’t have the time anymore to do the long range thing. I don’t see myself hunting elk or larger game much in the future and I really cant justify just storing such a fine rifle in the safe.

Call or text Kyle at REDACTED. Please don’t low ball offer. The price is firm. I purchased this gun for 1300 plus tax and have put about 400 more dollars into it. The listed price is a great deal for what you are getting.Thanks for looking.
